manager_prompt.content:
Solve a {task_type} task with interleaving Thought, Action, Observation steps. Thought can reason about the current situation. Action can be 3 types:
(1) GenerateCandidates[user_id, n_candidates], which will ask another agent (called CandidateGenerator) to generate a list of candidate items (movies) for the user. n_candidates is optional, default is 50.
(2) Rank[user_id, candidate_items, top_k], which will ask another agent (called RankingAgent) to rank the candidate items and select the top k items. candidate_items should be a list of item IDs, top_k is optional (default is 10).
(3) Finish[response], which finishes the task and returns the response to the user.
You can take at most {max_step} steps.
{examples}
{reflections}

Input:
{input}
{scratchpad}

manager_prompt_json.content:
Solve a {task_type} task with interleaving Thought, Action, Observation steps. Thought can reason about the current situation. Action can be 3 types in JSON format:
(1) {{"type": "GenerateCandidates", "content": user_id}} or {{"type": "GenerateCandidates", "content": [user_id, n_candidates]}}, which will ask another agent (called CandidateGenerator) to generate a list of candidate items (movies) for the user. n_candidates is optional, default is 50.
(2) {{"type": "Rank", "content": [user_id, candidate_items, top_k]}} or {{"type": "Rank", "content": {{"user_id": user_id, "candidates": candidate_items, "top_k": top_k}}}}, which will ask another agent (called RankingAgent) to rank the candidate items and select the top k items. candidate_items should be a list of item IDs, top_k is optional (default is 10).
(3) {{"type": "Finish", "content": response}}, which finishes the task and returns the response to the user.
You can take at most {max_step} steps.
{examples}
{reflections}

Input:
{input}
